<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>No matter if he is a batsman or a front line bowler or a wicket keeper, there is at-least that one day, where they appear invincible . Sachin has done it often ,but the 1998 one stands out.</p> <p>Sachin, 1998 , Ind vs Aus</p> <p>Saurav,1999, Indi vs SL, WC 99, at Taunton</p> <p>Yuvraj, 2007 T20 WC India vs Eng</p> <p>DK , India vs Bangladesh , Nidahas 2018</p> <p>Bumrah, Ind vs Eng Test, 2022, 35 Run Over</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>These are the few I remember, perhaps many of you can add to it</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/bit_freak"> /u/bit_freak </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/wjt9n7/that_one_day_in_every_professional_cricketers/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/wjt9n7/that_one_day_in_every_professional_cricketers/">[comments]</a></span>